      "side": 1,
      "message": "This seems fine as a std::string, since the input is already in std::string form.  However, I recommend making it \"const std::string\u0026\" to avoid a copy.\n\nYou won\u0027t be able to do +\u003d, but you can add a \".gif\" when passing it to PathUtils:\n\n    const std::string previewPath \u003d\n            PathUtils::join(getMacroPreviewsDirectory(), previewName + \".gif\");",
